WEBVTT

00:03.061 --> 00:04.011
Hey, did your parents let you

00:04.046 --> 00:05.696
Watch horror movies
at a young age?

00:05.731 --> 00:07.865
I remember when I went
to see <i>Jaws</i> for the first time.

00:07.899 --> 00:08.966
- How old were you?
- Eight.

00:09.001 --> 00:10.701
I had to be removed
from the theater.

00:10.736 --> 00:12.536
- [laughs]
- It was that traumatic?

00:12.570 --> 00:14.238
I remember it
was too intense for me,

00:14.272 --> 00:15.806
And my mom leaned over,
and was like, "are you okay?

00:15.840 --> 00:16.807
Do you want to stay
and watch it?"

00:16.841 --> 00:17.858
And I was like, "no."

00:17.893 --> 00:19.510
"Do you want
to go dress shopping?"

00:19.528 --> 00:21.678
[laughter]

00:21.697 --> 00:23.114
It's just weird,
like, nowadays,

00:23.148 --> 00:24.865
Like, you probably wouldn't even
think to take, you know,

00:24.916 --> 00:26.484
An eight- or nine-year-old
to a horror movie.

00:26.518 --> 00:27.818
When <i>Grizzly</i> came out,
I told my mom,

00:27.852 --> 00:28.819
"I want to see that,"
and she was like,

00:28.853 --> 00:29.904
"Are you sure?

00:29.955 --> 00:31.455
You remember what happened
in <i>Jaws?"</i>

00:31.490 --> 00:33.824
I was like, "No, I'm older now.
I can see <i>Grizzly."</i>

00:33.859 --> 00:36.360
There was a moment, the first
time the bear attacked somebody,

00:36.378 --> 00:40.081
And, like, off-camera,
you just see an arm fly by--

00:40.132 --> 00:41.549
A bloody arm fly by--

00:41.583 --> 00:43.367
And my mom looked at me,
and I was like, "Let's go."

00:43.402 --> 00:44.668
Then he got his period.

00:44.703 --> 00:47.204
[laughter]

